**Executive Summary**

**Overview:**

This project is a console-based C++ application that organizes recipes using Object-Oriented Programming principles. It enables users to add, view, edit, search, and delete categorized recipes (Starter, Main Course, Dessert).

**Key Findings:**

The project demonstrates strong use of OOP concepts including encapsulation, inheritance, and polymorphism. It also introduces basic menu-driven interaction and sets up a clean modular code structure ready for GUI integration in future phases.

**Introduction**

**Background:**

Object-Oriented Programming is essential in structuring real-world software. This project helps understand and implement core OOP concepts in a meaningful and hands-on way through recipe management.

**Project Objectives:**

- Build a working recipe manager using C++.
- Apply OOP principles practically.
- Implement categorized recipes using inheritance and polymorphism.
- Prepare a clean, scalable structure for future expansion (e.g., GUI).

**Project Description**

**Included:**

- Console-based recipe manager
- Categories: Starter, Main Course, Dessert
- Core features: add, view, search, edit, delete

**Excluded:**

- Meal planning
- File saving/loading
- GUI interface (planned for future)

**Technical Overview:**

- **Language:** C++
- **Compiler:** g++
- **IDE:** Visual Studio Code
- **Libraries:** Standard C++ (no vectors), planned GUI: SFML + TGUI

**Methodology**

**Approach:**

- Initial implementation of basic Recipe class
- Introduced RecipeManager for core functionality
- Added inheritance-based categories (StarterRecipe, etc.)
- Polymorphism added through Recipe\* array and virtual functions
- Final polish with search, edit, and delete features

**Roles and Responsibilities:**

All research, coding, testing, and documentation completed individually by the student.

**Project Implementation**

**Design and Structure:**

- Recipe (Base class with virtual functions)
- StarterRecipe, MainCourseRecipe, DessertRecipe (Child classes)
- RecipeManager class to manage an array of Recipe\*
- Modular file setup (Recipe.h, RecipeManager.h, etc.)

**Functionalities Developed:**

- Add Recipe (based on type)
- View All Recipes
- Search by Name
- Edit a Recipe
- Delete a Recipe

**Challenges Faced:**

- Managing polymorphism with pointers and dynamic memory
- Time management (project handled solo under a group scope)

**Results**

**Project Outcomes:**

- Fully working console application
- Demonstrated strong command of C++ and OOP
- Structured code ready for GUI integration
